channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Early voting begins in Nebraska and Washington, DC
item.description: Nebraska and the nation's capital began early voting on Monday as the majority of the country has now started gearing up for the 2024 election.

item.title: Kamala Harris trolls Trump at L.A. fundraiser full of celebrities
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris poked at Republican Donald Trump during a fancy fundraiser on Sunday, telling donors that as she campaigns around the country her "crowds are pretty big" - before heading to Nevada for a rally at the same venue where the GOP nominee appeared two weeks ago.

item.title: Kamala Harris’s Attack on the Filibuster Puts ‘Democracy on the Ballot’
item.description: Harris’s proposal shows the folly of conflating ‘democratic norms’ with the political success of the Democratic Party.

item.title: Hurricane Helene Fallout Shows Why America Can’t Afford Another Potemkin Presidency
item.description: Americans throughout several southeastern states are enduring catastrophic devastation caused by Hurricane Helene. So naturally, America’s lamebrain Democrat president and vice president are missing in action. After making landfall in Florida late last week, the Category 4 hurricane ripped across the Southeast over the weekend, producing massive flooding and mudslides. At least 110 people across […]

item.title: Critical battles loom as Congress looks to avoid crippling 'shutdown crisis' for next president
item.description: Congressional lawmakers have left Washington, D.C., for six weeks and will return to a radically different political playing field in November.

item.title: Trump escalates attacks on Harris' mental fitness and suggests she should be prosecuted
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump escalated his personal attacks on his Democratic rival, Kamala Harris, on Sunday by repeating an insult that she was "mentally impaired" while also saying she should be "impeached and prosecuted."

item.title: It’s Time to End Our Fed Obsession and Refocus on Growth
item.description: Long-term, broad-based economic growth is the goal, and the Fed alone cannot deliver it.

item.title: Biden Lounged At The Beach While Floods Wreaked ‘Biblical Devastation’ On Appalachia
item.description: Biden remained lounging at the beach this weekend while Appalachian valleys in North Carolina and Tennessee suffered deadly flooding.

item.title: Senate GOP teams up to take on Harris policy pitfalls in pre-election video series
item.description: Senate Republicans are releasing a video series showcasing a timeline of Kamala Harris' "failures" on the border, inflation and foreign policy.

item.title: Rubio rips the Biden administration for failing to define 'victory' in the Ukraine-Russian war
item.description: Sen. Marco Rubio slammed the Biden administration for not "defining" what the end of the Ukraine-Russian war will look like and said it will only end with a "negotiated settlement."

item.title: Kamala Harris Is an Enemy of the Second Amendment
item.description: Her record is more hostile toward gun ownership than that of any presidential candidate in history.

item.title: NY Judges Scrutinize ‘Troubling’ $450 Million Penalty In Trump Fraud Case: ‘No One Lost Any Money’
item.description: A New York appellate court is raising questions regarding the penalty and the justification under which AG Letitia James brought the case.

item.title: How to watch the Fox News - CBS News Vice Presidential Debate Simulcast
item.description: The first and likely only vice presidential debate between Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz and Ohio Sen. JD Vance to be broadcast on CBS News and simulcast across Fox platforms.

item.title: California governor vetoes bill to create first-in-nation AI safety measures
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom vetoed a landmark bill aimed at establishing first-in-the-nation safety measures for large artificial intelligence models Sunday.

item.title: Life in Your Face
item.description: On Stefan Zweig’s novel Beware of Pity , eloquent and raw.

item.title: Report: 647K Noncitizens Convicted Or Suspected Of Homicide, Other Crimes Are Not In ICE Custody
item.description: More than 647,000 illegal immigrants convicted or suspected of sexual assault, homicide, and other heinous crimes are roaming free in the United States, federal immigration authorities confirmed on Wednesday. The revelation came in a letter sent to Rep. Tony Gonzales, R-Texas, by U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) Deputy Director and Senior Official Performing the […]

item.title: Newsom vetoes bill to establish first-in-nation AI safety regulations in California
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom vetoed a bill to create safety measures for large artificial intelligence models in what would have been the first such law in the country.

item.title: Majority of likely U.S. voters want proof of citizenship law, pollsters say
item.description: "Voters overwhelmingly believe proof of citizenship should be required for voting in American elections, after Congress recently avoided a government shutdown over the issue," Rasmussen Reports advises.

item.title: A Master of the Tall Tale
item.description: Glen Rounds, a son of the American West, spun rip-roaring tales that are perfect for reading aloud.

item.title: Washington Post’s Incurious Philip Bump Says The Media Should Just Give Kamala The ‘Benefit Of The Doubt’
item.description: Bump is ready to quickly move on from any issue that could be a problem for the political party he's trying to help win this election.
